title: Malaysian Food Festival launched in ShanghaiTravelandtourworld.com
text:
Malaysian Food Festival launched in Shanghai  
The “Malaysian Food Festival” has been launched in Shanghai in line with the Malaysia Kitchen Programme by the Malaysia External Trade Development Corporation (Matrade).
The event has been organised in partnership with the Shanghai Marriott Hotel City Centre to roll-out Malaysian cuisine from Oct 14-Nov 28, said Matrade’s Trade Commissioner in Shanghai, Mansor Shah Wahid.
“The hotel is targeting about 200 people to dine-in daily with people loving the taste of Malaysian cuisine,” he added.
The aim of the programme is to promote Malaysian cuisine, as well as enhance opportunities for trade in products spanning food to non-food and services.
The event was officiated by Tourism and Culture Minister Nazri Abdul Aziz on Wednesday night (Oct 14) which was also attended by Consul General of Malaysia in Shanghai, Tan Yang Thai and Shanghai Marriott Hotel City Centre’s hotel manager, Jessie Zhang.
